Re: 値段が高いレストランはあまり好きじゃな ---- I MEAN WHAT?
by becki_kanou » Sat 01.08.2011 6:19 pm The sentence is fine as it is. It is a common modifying phrase XがY,Z and can usually be rephrased with の as well as が.髪が（の）長い少女= A girl with long hair足が(の)速い学生 = a student with fast legs (i.e. who runs quickly)値段が（の）高いレストラン= a restaurant with high prices(Ninja'd by Nilecat since I took too long, but I'll post it anyway.)
そうだ、嬉しいんだ、生きる喜び！
例え胸の傷が痛んでも。
