Re: 値段が高いレストランはあまり好きじゃな ---- I MEAN WHAT?
by Ongakuka » Mon 01.10.2011 10:35 pm nedan ga takai resutoran wa amari suki janaiI'm pretty sure this is fine, but you could also say 'nedan no takai resutoran wa amari suki janai.'takai nedan resutoran wa amari suki janai....For this you definitely need to insert 'no' between 'takai' and 'nedan' : 'takai nedan no resutoran wa amai suki janai.'
なぜなら、おまえは・・・・・・人形だ
